item.title: Project-2: Modal Choices Prediction of urban workers from home to work
item.description: This Project is a continuation of my internship in CETUD where I modeled modal choices of workers using econometric modeling. The objective is to train a prediction-oriented model of Machine Learning to predict modal choices of workers according to the distance, time, cost and revenu.

item.title: Project-1:SPSS and Excel Training Session
item.description: This training is to strengthen skills of the supervisors and professionals of the AJSE in terms of analysis and manipulation of data, essential in the professional environment. The members of the association will be the only beneficiaries. At the end of this training, they will be able to manage with more efficiency the tasks relating to the activities carried out in the association by using the powerful tools of MS Excel.
